data.description: This beautiful 4 bedroom, 3 full bath home is located in the desirable Portrait Hill subdivision. Conveniently located near the interstate just off the Peak exit, close to restaurants and shopping and zoned for the Award Winning Lexington Richland 5 school district. Chapin Middle school just a short walk away. This floorplan features and open concept with the primary and 2 additional bedrooms on the main, and a second primary suite on the second floor perfect for in-laws, guests or flex space. The kitchen boasts granite countertops, stainless appliances, tiled backsplash, kitchen island, pantry, eat in, an in wall brew express coffee station, and under and above cabinet lighting. There is common area next to the property that no one will build on. Sit back and relax with a cup of coffee on the back screened in porch overlooking the lovely landscaping with a blueberry bush, fig tree, crape myrtles all within a fully fenced in backyard. Possibilities are endless with this 11x16 workshop with a mini split and power and a sidewalk leading around to the side entry garage. Seller had installed a reverse osmosis water filtration system and replaced the tub shower in the guest bath to a full low threshold shower. Transferable termite bond!  Community pool, clubhouse and playground! Make this house your home today!
